      <dsc>
         <c id="ref10" level="series">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Inventory</unittitle>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_e0c6e0bcecdc5f28c0ed22f3f893007b">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>These papers consist almost entirely of the correspondence of Narcissus Graham (1762-1829) from 1774 to 1786. Graham was persuaded in 1776 to enlist in the Revolutionary Army. A resident of Suffield, Connecticut, he joined the Fife and Drum Corps of the Fourth Connecticut Regiment. His letters to various family members describe vividly battles in Connecticut, New York, and New Jersey, and delineate the under-fed, ill-clothed condition of the army, especially during the coldest winter in many years. Despite Graham's great unhappiness with such a life, he remained with the army until 1783.</p>
            </scopecontent>
